Text.Value: Welcome back, True Soul.
Not to your taste?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Rubbing her neck where Astarion bit her
EditorData.NodeContext: Rubbing her neck where Astarion bit her

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion bites into her neck, she is very clearly enjoying it. To Astarion the blood tastes foul, though.

Text.Value: You want to be bitten?
I'm not certain I'll have time.
I hope you find it as satisfying as I found this.
Thankfully, I wasn't in it at the time.

EditorData.NodeContext: Smiling - we've brought up the fact that her family is supposed to have been wiped out, she responds mildy, not being drawn

Text.Value: YHURGH!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Overcome by the wretched taste of her blood, Astarion breaks off his bite, turns away from Araj, and vomits up the blood he was drinking.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KD] Astarion vommiting and the sound of the vommit splashing on the ground

Text.Value: What kind of proposal?
'Many hearts, one soul' - isn't that how the blessing goes? We are all one under the Absolute.
Do you have a name, spawn?
Incredible. Incredible!

EditorData.NodeContext: Being bitten by a vampire, having an AMAZING experience

Text.Value: Speak to me again if you'd like to hear more. I'll be waiting.
I just want to see your normal stock for now.
You aren't working for Cazador, are you?
Well - it'll certainly do something, my most noble vindicator.
Now, now. A True Soul ought to know their doctrine. I've picked a little up in my time here.

EditorData.logicalname: Alias (ASTARION NOT HERE, BUT IN TEAM)

Text.Value: 'Unnatural' - are we not all one under the Absolute, True Soul? Surely there's nothing more natural than sharing our resources.
A little pain for a lot of gold. And...

EditorData.NodeContext: The 'And...' is leading to her giving us an additional item

Text.Value: Bite her.
Oh? I'm afraid I have quite enough for my purposes - from you, at least.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not interested, but still friendly. We've served our purpose but might send some friends her way

Text.Value: Oh I'd prefer if you did.
Rest and return. I'll feel better buying your blood when I know you can actually spare it.
Welcome back, True Soul! You've come in the spirit of trade, I hope?
There we are. All of your very best traits in a bottle. Use it well!
What kind of potion can you make?
With one drop, I can brew a rather potent potion for you. The rest, I keep for myself.

EditorData.NodeContext: Pleasant - this is of course a perfectly normal thing to offer

Text.Value: It's not 'True Soul' blood you want. It's illithid-tainted blood.
It's not for sale, but it's yours if you bite me.
I gave you my answer.
All right. Let's do it.
Just a little prick and it's all over. Close your eyes.

EditorData.AnimationTags: Merchant Araj leans forward to do some blood drawing action. The PLYR also holds out there arm, and winces slightly as their blood is drawn. <LoganP>

Text.Value: I've changed my mind - I will bite you.
And if I may - would you have a moment to discuss another more personal matter.

EditorData.logicalname: ASTARION NOT HERE, BUT IN TEAM

Text.Value: Oblodra? That House was destroyed a century ago.
Should you be interested, I have a particular offer I'd like to make.

EditorData.NodeContext: Taking a moment to size us up to see if she wants to offer us this deal - resolves she does

Text.Value: *Realisation washes over you. Every drow knows of the purge of House Oblodra - but you remember the whispers of why.*

EditorData.NodeContext: (Oblodra = o-BLOD-ruh)

Text.Value: *Among the many crimes tallied against them - their reckless experimentation with illithid breeding-stock.*
No one gave it to me. Rather ironically, it runs in the bloodline. We Oblodras are naturally curious folk. Always have been.
Very well, if that's your answer. But you know where to find me if you change your mind.
Very well. If there's anything else you need, let me know.
I- I must prepare myself for his arrival...

EditorData.NodeContext: flustered

Text.Value: To feel your life's blood slipping away? To dance on the edge between life and death? Yes, I want it.
You're really a vampire? At least one of their spawn...
Absolutely not.
Show me your stock.
That is not a name which has ever passed my lips. I am a friend to you, I wish to be a friend to him.
So let me adjust my offer. Your blood and your silence in exchange for the potions I mention - and a tidy pile of gold besides.

EditorData.NodeContext: Unfazed, happy - proposing a deal she knows we'll take.

Text.Value: To feel your life's blood slipping away? To dance on the edge between life and death? Yes, I want it.
I want to trade my blood for a potion.
We can learn exactly what that means together, hm?
*You realise why the name rings familiar: House Oblodra was purged a century ago by an alliance of rival drow houses.*

EditorData.NodeContext: (Oblodra = o-BLOD-ruh)

Text.Value: ...'Blessed' by the Absolute, but not blinded by it? Now I simply must study you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wicked grin - we've just revealed ourselves to be an even more valuable asset than she thought

Text.Value: *As her blood seeps between your lips, you realise something's off. Her blood is rancid, tainted by unnatural experiments.*
I know you travel with a delightful night-walker in your retinue.
Ah, well... if you don't mind me saying, you don't look entirely well.

EditorData.NodeContext: We've agreed to let her draw blood, but our health is too low. She's trying to tell us we look terrible, but politely

Text.Value: Good. Now, Astarion, I've dreamt of being bitten by a vampire since I was a young girl.
Excuse me? This is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity and you're squandering it.
My cousins did like to boast about their view over the Clawrift. Now their bones decorate the bottom.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sighing, a sad thing but can't be helped (she does not miss this extended family)

Text.Value: Keep your gold. I want to see what the cult does to non-believers.
Araj Oblodra, trader in blood and the sanguineous arts. But you, True Soul...
Goodness, no. Nothing so unsanitary. The Oblodras clan practise their own form of blood alchemy.
If you know of any other True Souls willing to aid my research, though, do send them my way.
Research, naturally. We Oblodras are simply curious by nature.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrugging - she doesn't want to to be drawn on her true motive. (Oblodra = o-BLOD-ruh)

Text.Value: I will have to decline.

EditorData.NodeContext: Through slightly gritted teeth

Text.Value: Blood rituals? Unnatural heresy. I will not.
Ever since I was a young girl I have dreamt of being bitten by a vampire.
Araj Oblodra, trader in all things occult. A very great pleasure to meet you, True Soul.

EditorData.NodeContext: Chirpy and confident - she's standing in the heart of darkness but unfazed. (Araj Oblodra = a-RADJ o-BLOD-ruh)

Text.Value: I want to trade my blood for a potion.
Don't worry, we're all friends under the Absolute. I won't bite.
This is blasphemy. My blood is sacred.
I'm sorry? You want to be bitten?
It was everything I imagined. And then more. I'll be able to put this to good use.
Astarion, but hold on-

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: cut off before he can finish speaking

Text.Value: My vampiric friend? Sure, I can bring him here.
Blood magic is an... unusual talent. Who gave it to you?
Just a little, I promise. I have a 'special offer' of sorts for True Souls. It might interest you.
Come back any time.
If it'll help me vanquish my foes - fine.
Put plainly - I'd like your blood. A vial of True Soul's blood, specifically.

EditorData.NodeContext: Satisfied - we're getting on to the topic she cares most about. States her strange request plainly.

Text.Value: It's not for sale, but it's yours if you bite me.
Don't say such a thing. Don't dash my hope.
I will speak of it when he is here. Not before. But it will be to your advantage, I promise.
I'm not sure - my blood is exceptionally sought after.
Never mind. I'm not interested.
The beings you speak of have no use for gods - and yet here we stand in a church of their making.
There is malice in this blood. It boils, churns, and whispers to me.
Well, that's why we're trading, no? I assure you, the potions are more than worth their weight.
I hear you trade potions for True Soul blood.
Unless they are not the makers, but simply the means. Wouldn't that be a secret worth knowing?
And now here I stand before one. Can you make my dream come true?
Let's hear about this special offer of yours.
Excellent! I knew you'd come around.
Truth be told, I heard tell of your coming before you arrived. Ketheric's dogs prowl far and wide round the Tower.
And what exactly are you planning to do with your share?
How unfortunate. But if you won't take my blood, then perhaps I could have yours?
I feel exquisite though - so here's my part of the bargain.
I'll even compensate you - a potion of legendary power that forever increases the strength of the one who consumes it.
Please. I have a proposal for him. I will reward you both, handsomely.
I read about your kind for so many years, but never thought I'd find one in real life. And to find such a fine specimen...
I'll even compensate you - a potion of legendary power that forever increases the strength of the one who consumes it.
A Zhengyian blood mage? Unusual for you to be so far from Vaasa.
No idea! But it will be unique to you - your blood essence and the Absolute's blessing intertwined.

EditorData.NodeContext: Cheerful and excited - she's genuinely curious to see what our blood will do

Text.Value: Leave.
I have a project to complete - and you are far too unique a specimen to risk.
That, I cannot allow. For either of us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Regretful, but otherwise unfazed by our threat

Text.Value: If you can't be reasonable, I'll just have to observe your development from afar. For now.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: She bows at the end (disappears in gameplay immediately after)
EditorData.NodeContext: Nodding to herself, resolving reluctantly on  leaving us for now lest we expose her. Bows at end (she simply disappears a moment later)

Synopsis:
A merchant selling in the bazaar on the ground floor of Moonrise Tower. She is very interested in illithid-tainted blood from each race, which when traded grants a different kind of potion as a reward. The player can also learn her house's origins - and the fact that she's here to research the illithids.


For nodes marked as OOM AND COM are in their own dialog file

1. Araj
2. Group_Players (that might include Astarion since the default dialog and AOM version are pretty much the same).
